  I ruptured two discs in my back while performing borderline slave labor at a shady warehouse in Delco, PA that was run by a low IQ demon named Sal. Upon confirming the severity of my injury, I was prescribed 120 Percocet per month and I embarked upon a two and a half year descent into the darkest depths of prescription painkiller addiction. Sure, I was evicted, had my beloved Chrysler 300, The Perc Mobile, repo’d and blew through every dollar I had, but the worst part was far more macabre than anyone could imagine: Every thought I had during the Perc Era was immortalized in a collection of Facebook posts. The hundreds upon hundreds of Perc posts are so embarrassing that I am left with no choice but to put them all in a book and offer a post by post analysis of every humiliating thought.


